00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:35,400
of the workday. And I was like, I'm just not 
sure where to take things and what we're doing  

647
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:40,880
right now. And it was so interesting to hear 
his perspective of, in his world, everything  

648
00:59:40,880 --> 00:59:45,240
was actually going pretty reasonably well. It 
was like, we kind of knew, he had his roadmap,  

649
00:59:45,240 --> 00:59:49,800
he knew what to go build. He had the next feature, 
the next three weeks of sprints planned out or  

650
00:59:49,800 --> 00:59:53,640
something like this. And he was like, oh, the 
